# Storytelling authoring (mandatory)

[`docs/storytelling.md`](docs/storytelling.md) is a **mentor conversation** for an inexperienced developer: *why* we build the blog/CMS this way and how decisions connect. It is **not** a second roadmap, not a lesson, not a file list.

**Canonical example:** current structure in `docs/storytelling.md` (chapters I–XIII, Track 2 split into X–XIII). **Do not regress** to a single chapter with `NNN — service — HTTP` chains.

## Role of each doc

| Document | Answers |
| -------- | ------- |
| **storytelling** | Why? How does this fit the story? What links to earlier chapters? |
| **learning-path** | In what order? |
| **lesson-NNN** | What to run, which files, verification |
| **development-roadmap** | Step done / next (source of truth for status) |

## Chapter template

Every chapter (including new ones for Track 3+) uses this skeleton. **Do not** add `### Шаг NNN` per sprint.

| Section | Purpose |
| ------- | ------- |
| **Сцена** | Metaphor / situation a beginner recognizes |
| **Что болит** | Cost of skipping this chapter |
| **Намерение** | One intent for the whole chapter |
| **Как это сложилось у нас** / **Как это выглядело в нашем проекте** | 3–6 paragraphs, **story arcs** — not step-by-step |
| **Связь с прошлым** | 3–5 bullets: «поэтому…» links to earlier chapters (required Track 2+) |
| **Что стоит унести** | Takeaways for the reader |
| **Уроки этой главы** | One table only: step \| one-line gist \| lesson link |

Track 0–1 chapters (I–IX) may use «Как это выглядело» instead of «Как это сложилось»; same rules apply.

## After each roadmap step

1. Pick the **right chapter** from storytelling TOC (I–XIII today). New track arc → **new chapter**, never append a changelog to the bottom of one chapter.
2. Add **one row** to «Уроки этой главы» for that step.
3. Add **2–4 sentences** to the chapter **arc** (integrate into existing narrative; do not start a new paragraph that lists step numbers).
4. Update **«Связь с прошлым»** only if the link is new and non-obvious.
5. Refresh **«Где мы сейчас»** and **«Что дальше»** as a short **checkpoint** (~3 paragraphs + link to roadmap) — no endpoint lists, no service/class names.

## Forbidden in storytelling prose

- Chains like `**057** — TypeORM … **058** — DATABASE_URL …`
- Blocks «После NNN …» after the chapter table
- Copying lesson Verification, Changed Files, commands, env var names, HTTP paths
- Duplicating roadmap «done» lists in «Где мы сейчас»
- Extra tables that repeat lesson indexes
- `### Шаг` / one H3 per roadmap step inside a chapter

## Allowed and encouraged

- Metaphors (редакция, ресторан, рейс — same tone as chapters I–IX)
- Plain language; minimal identifiers (say «единый формат ошибок», not `ProblemDetailsFilter`)
- Explicit **connections** across tracks (e.g. redaction before auth; problem+json → friendly 409)
- One **Уроки этой главы** table at chapter end — index only

## Anti-pattern vs good arc

**Bad (changelog):**

> **063** — AuthModule register … **064** — unique email 409 … **065** — login …

**Good (arc + connection):**

> Регистрация и вход стали продуктовыми маршрутами с ответами из общих контрактов. Дубликат email и неверный пароль не раскрывают внутренности БД — тот же Problem Details, что мы настроили в главе VI. Refresh живёт отдельно от access: украденный долгий токен не переживает ротацию.

## Splitting chapters (Track 2+ model)

When a track grows beyond one **intent**, split into multiple TOC chapters (example: X memory, XI sessions, XII account lifecycle, XIII permissions). Each chapter = one reader question, not «everything in auth».

## Global sections

| Section | Style |
| ------- | ----- |
| **Большая цель** | Product picture + 3–4 sentences «where we are now» for a newcomer |
| **Где мы сейчас** | Editorial metaphor + one paragraph per completed track + «not in product yet» + link to roadmap |
| **Что дальше** | 2–3 sentences + roadmap link; no duplicate «stub table» of done features |
| **Сквозные принципы** | Timeless rules; principle 8: storytelling is history, not changelog |

## Agent checklist before marking a sprint done

- [ ] Correct chapter (or new chapter) updated, not a growing blob at end of file
- [ ] Table row added; arc extended by 2–4 sentences only
- [ ] No forbidden patterns in diff
- [ ] «Где мы сейчас» / «Что дальше» still readable by a non-coder

